title: Brazil’s Lula promised to save democracy. Why is he embracing Maduro?
description: The Brazilian leader's welcome was another stop in the diplomatic comeback of Venezuela's socialist authoritarian.

title: Chinese jet conducts ‘aggressive’ move on U.S. surveillance plane
description: The Pentagon released video appearing to show a Chinese military jet intercepting a U.S. surveillance plane over the South China Sea.

title: Real-life ‘Morning Show’ meltdown grips Britain with sex, lies and betrayal
description: Star TV host Phillip Schofield admitted to an affair with a younger colleague, causing outrage and sparking a rift with ITV co-star Holly Willoughby.

title: Woman is knocked unconscious in famous cheese-rolling race – and wins
description: Canadian Delaney Irving woke up in a medical tent to learn she won the women's cheese-roll race in Gloucestershire, England, a tradition dating back centuries.

title: Drones hit Moscow, shocking Russian capital after new missile attack on Kyiv
description: Drones damaged two residential buildings in a dramatic strike on Moscow after yet another barrage of Russian missiles on Kyiv killed one person and injured more than 12 on Tuesday.

title: How the U.S. wants to pressure China to help avert climate catastrophe
description: U.S.-China relations will determine the future of global warming, but it's difficult to set aside superpower rivalries in the bid to reduce emissions.

title: An alleged Russian spy whale turned up in Sweden. Why?
description: The beluga whale, known as Hvaldimir, was spotted in Sweden after appearing last week in Oslo. He might be seeking human interaction, one expert said.

title: Japan’s leader fires aide — his son — after party at official residence
description: Japanese Prime Minister Fumio Kishida had been accused by opponents of nepotism after appointing his son, Shotaro, as a government aide.

title: Ukraine live briefing: Russia attacks Kyiv three times in 24 hours, reports drone strike in Moscow
description: Moscow's mayor said drones hit two residential buildings in the Russian capital. That report came after Russia conducted its third aerial attack on the Ukrainian capital in 24 hours.

title: Erdogan becomes an era-defining electoral autocrat
description: Even as President Recep Tayyip Erdogan consolidated his rule over two decades, political scholars still saw Turkey as a quasi-democracy. That view is starting to change as Erdogan renews his mandate for power.
